      </div>
      
      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
        The nine planets (Navagrahas) in Vedic Astrology each govern specific aspects of life. The Sun represents the soul and father, Moon governs emotions and mother, Mars controls energy and courage, Mercury rules communication, Jupiter brings wisdom and growth, Venus influences love and beauty, Saturn teaches discipline, Rahu and Ketu provide spiritual lessons.
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
        The twelve houses represent different life areas: 1st house (personality), 2nd house (wealth), 3rd house (siblings), 4th house (home), 5th house (children), 6th house (health), 7th house (marriage), 8th house (transformation), 9th house (spirituality), 10th house (career), 11th house (gains), and 12th house (liberation).
      </p>

      <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-6">
        Nakshatras, or lunar mansions, add another layer of depth. These 27 constellations provide insights into personality traits, life purpose, and timing of events, making Vedic Astrology incredibly precise and personalized.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-8 mb-4">Why People Still Trust Jyotish</h2>
      
